  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uganda Deaf Awareness and Communication (U-DAC) Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Deaf children often don&#x2019;t go to school in Uganda because they have trouble communicating, and teachers lack the skills to work with them. Even their own families often think they won&#x2019;t be able to learn. This project will test an approach that has worked in Malawi to give deaf children an education. It will train local teachers,and leaders in the community as well as deaf children themselves and their families. It will teach them sign language, finger spelling and lip reading.Through this work, more deaf children to will attend schools and get a good quality education.</narrative>
  </description>
